Get a newer version of JUnit or try the swingui - one or both of those
solutions should yield a better error message.  Older JUnit versions used to
swallow exceptions that happen on startup of test runs.  You can also hack
the testrunner class itself and recompile to make it print the real
exception instead of that useless &quot;Could not invoke the suite() method&quot;
message.

